1
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:42,060
=Twin Fire Dawn=

2
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:45,060
=Episode 12=

3
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:47,180
(Kasili)

4
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:48,259
The Fragrance Gala?

5
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:49,660
What's the Fragrance Gala?

6
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,379
It may look like

7
00:00:51,380 --> 00:00:53,580
they're selling perfume and spices,

8
00:00:53,980 --> 00:00:56,020
but behind the scenes,
they're dealing opium.

9
00:00:56,180 --> 00:00:57,179
Just like those people.

10
00:00:57,180 --> 00:00:58,140
Nothing but hypocrisy.

11
00:01:01,100 --> 00:01:02,060
Yunqiu.

12
00:01:02,260 --> 00:01:03,700
Are you sure?

13
00:01:04,540 --> 00:01:06,379
But I think the Commander

14
00:01:06,380 --> 00:01:08,100
is actually a good person.

15
00:01:08,380 --> 00:01:10,220
He even takes care of orphans.

16
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:13,020
I almost got fooled by him too.

17
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:17,699
If that's the case,

18
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:19,220
then we have to expose him.

19
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:20,420
Yunqiu.

20
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:21,740
Be careful no matter what.

21
00:01:22,540 --> 00:01:23,520
Wait for my message.

22
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:26,000
The moment I get the evidence,
I'll call the newspaper office immediately.

23
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:26,540
Alright.

24
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:28,379
Then I'll tell my coworkers

25
00:01:28,380 --> 00:01:29,939
to stay late and get ready.

26
00:01:29,940 --> 00:01:31,419
As soon as we get your evidence,

27
00:01:31,420 --> 00:01:32,860
we'll prepare the papers for print.

28
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:35,899
Then I should get going.

29
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,139
Wait for my message tomorrow.

30
00:01:37,140 --> 00:01:37,820
Okay.

31
00:01:58,020 --> 00:02:00,020
Thank you for your hard work.
This way, please.

32
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:16,300
Why did you come back?

33
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:20,700
I didn't really feel like
going to the concert anymore.

34
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:22,620
I wanted to stay home with you.

35
00:02:35,220 --> 00:02:36,899
Last night, it was because

36
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:38,700
I was worried about your condition.

37
00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:40,819
You've only just recovered.

38
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:43,340
And as your wife,

39
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:45,660
shouldn't I be helping you receive guests?

40
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,540
Alright.

41
00:02:56,340 --> 00:02:57,940
I'd like that too.

42
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:04,620
Welcome, everyone,
to the Commander's Residence

43
00:03:05,180 --> 00:03:07,140
for this year's Fragrance Gala.

44
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:09,580
My wife and I

45
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:11,659
have specially gathered

46
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:14,140
rare perfumes and spices
from both home and abroad.

47
00:03:14,620 --> 00:03:18,300
We hope you'll all enjoy
a truly unforgettable evening.

48
00:03:43,370 --> 00:03:45,050
- This one isn't bad either.
- Indeed.

49
00:03:47,810 --> 00:03:48,849
Understood.

50
00:03:48,850 --> 00:03:50,219
You prefer lighter scents.

51
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:51,080
Right.

52
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,410
Then let's head over there.

53
00:03:55,020 --> 00:03:56,660
Every perfume here

54
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,380
has such a unique fragrance.

55
00:04:07,020 --> 00:04:08,300
No perfume here

56
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:11,660
could ever compare to your scent.

57
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:16,180
Perfume is actually
a very special kind of gift.

58
00:04:16,420 --> 00:04:17,540
How so?

59
00:04:18,260 --> 00:04:19,540
For example,

60
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:22,020
you could give me a bottle of perfume.

61
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:23,460
If I wear it every day,

62
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:25,739
then whenever you
catch that scent again,

63
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:27,580
you'll naturally think of me.

64
00:04:34,170 --> 00:04:35,100
You're right.

65
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:37,409
It's citrus, isn't it?

66
00:04:37,410 --> 00:04:38,550
Too sweet.

67
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:47,940
Looks like I should learn
a thing or two today.

68
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:49,430
That's true.

69
00:04:59,580 --> 00:05:01,180
What do you think of this one?

70
00:05:04,780 --> 00:05:06,100
A pure sweetness

71
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:09,540
with a mysterious allure.

72
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:14,460
It suits you perfectly.

73
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:18,500
Then let's take this one.

74
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:19,899
Thank you.

75
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:20,900
I really like it.

76
00:05:22,540 --> 00:05:24,420
Commander,
commander-in-Chief Li has arrived.

77
00:05:27,820 --> 00:05:29,540
Wait here for me a moment.

78
00:05:29,740 --> 00:05:32,220
I'll go greet Commander-in-Chief Li.

79
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:34,740
Alright. I'll go touch up my makeup first.

80
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:45,060
(This is the perfect chance
to look for evidence.)

81
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:31,700
Commander-in-Chief, this way please.

82
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:45,300
Commander-in-Chief.

83
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:46,819
This way please.

84
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:47,620
Mm.

85
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:02,420
The opium is in Warehouse No. 2.

86
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:03,220
Right.

87
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:06,460
Tonight, this shipment must
be sent out no matter what.

88
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,940
Handle it the usual way.

89
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,420
Naturally.

90
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:14,940
Keep this safe.

91
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:18,100
This is...

92
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:21,659
These are the names
of the merchants selling our goods.

93
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:22,459
Tonight,

94
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:25,139
that shipment from Warehouse No. 2

95
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:26,260
must be delivered.

96
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:28,099
This shipment is extremely important.

97
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,620
There can't be any mistakes.

98
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:30,460
Understood.

99
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,180
Nianchi.

100
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:17,460
This is a special opportunity
I've given you.

101
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:20,620
Don't repeat
what happened three years ago.

102
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:23,700
Back then, the Zhuang family
secretly held back the shipment.

103
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:27,660
Of course,

104
00:08:28,380 --> 00:08:29,420
I was also at fault

105
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:30,900
for misjudging people.

106
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:32,900
That won't happen again,
Commander-in-Chief.

107
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:36,100
Have you found the opium
the Zhuang family hid?

108
00:08:37,580 --> 00:08:38,660
We're still searching.

109
00:08:38,740 --> 00:08:40,300
You'd better move faster.

110
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:42,580
My patience is limited.

111
00:08:43,340 --> 00:08:44,580
I'm sorry, Commander-in-Chief.

112
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:49,899
Nianchi.

113
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:52,859
Three years ago,
you followed me into battle.

114
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:53,659
Back then,

115
00:08:53,660 --> 00:08:54,859
you were full of spirit

116
00:08:54,860 --> 00:08:56,220
and undefeated in every fight.

117
00:08:56,780 --> 00:09:00,459
You even saved my life during a crisis.

118
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:01,340
That's why

119
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:02,859
I promoted you

120
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:04,740
to Commander of Yancheng.

121
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:13,100
You and I are on the same boat.

122
00:09:13,580 --> 00:09:16,060
Don't disappoint me.

123
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:18,760
Rest assured, Commander-in-Chief.

124
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,620
I'll handle it immediately.

125
00:09:22,060 --> 00:09:22,860
Good.

126
00:09:25,380 --> 00:09:26,840
This way please, Commander-in-Chief.

127
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:16,740
Cheng Yi.

128
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:32,680
(The opium is in Warehouse No. 2)

129
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:46,580
Stop right there.

130
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:53,820
(Investigation into Yancheng
Opium Addiction Groups)

131
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:55,779
Why do you have

132
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,860
the document I gave the Commander?

133
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,760
(Investigation into Yancheng
Opium Addiction Groups)

134
00:11:10,570 --> 00:11:15,260
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

135
00:11:16,570 --> 00:11:21,890
♪How much hope must fade into despair?♪

136
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:25,970
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

137
00:11:26,310 --> 00:11:29,320
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

138
00:11:29,490 --> 00:11:34,610
♪You and I caught in
this tangled love and hate♪

139
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:40,920
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

140
00:11:41,980 --> 00:11:47,580
♪How many times
must pain cut deep before we wake?♪

141
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:51,500
♪I once gave myself
to you so completely♪

142
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:54,699
♪Still holding on to that heart♪

143
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:59,839
♪Only to suffer your fatal blow♪

144
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:04,159
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

145
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,739
♪Yet I approach you with such caution♪

146
00:12:06,740 --> 00:12:09,019
♪How could a stand in ever have♪

147
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:12,569
♪The right to be loved by you?♪

148
00:12:12,570 --> 00:12:17,099
♪If love is nothing
more than endless schemes♪

149
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:19,630
♪Used and abandoned in the end♪

150
00:12:19,770 --> 00:12:21,719
♪Still I walk into♪

151
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:25,319
♪The trap you set without regret♪

152
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:29,369
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

153
00:12:29,370 --> 00:12:31,949
♪Yet keep it buried deep inside♪

154
00:12:31,950 --> 00:12:34,109
♪A stand in can never cross♪

155
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:37,549
♪The shortest distance between us♪

156
00:12:37,550 --> 00:12:42,520
♪If love can
make someone lose themselves♪

157
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:47,350
♪Then let me stay by your side♪

158
00:12:50,130 --> 00:12:51,699
♪A substitute♪

159
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:56,700
♪Needs no reason♪

